    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "They will just compete with each other at signing blocks, most probably making a mini fork at every step when it's their turn to sign. If you have only one single authorised signer but multiple nodes playing that role, they might each start signing their own chain and ignore the other, or not. It's kind of undefined behavior. The protocol won't be hurt, but you might end up in weird situations.",
